# {{substub}}

In U.S. history, any Southerner who supported the federal plan of Reconstruction after the Civil War or who joined with the black freedman and the carpetbaggers in support of Republican Party policies. These supporters came from various segments of Southern society. In the Deep South many were apt to be former Whigs of the planter–merchant aristocracy. The term is pejorative.

